class Solution {
    public boolean canVisitAllRooms(List<List<Integer>> rooms) {
        int n = rooms.size();
        boolean[] visited = new boolean[n];

        for (List<Integer> keyList : rooms) {
            for (int key : keyList) {
                if (!visited[key - 1]) {
                    visited[key - 1] = true;
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^2)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

We iterate through the rooms list once to process each key. Then, for each key, we check if it has been visited before. If not, we mark it as visited and return true, indicating that we can visit all rooms. If we reach a room where all keys have been visited, we return false, indicating that we cannot visit all rooms.

